        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 5:54PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alice, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alice, San Diego, Ben Bolt, Alice Acres, Palito Blanco, and Lake
Alice.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 668 and 686.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
